            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-04-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On December 27, 1949, the United States announced that talks would open with Cuba
                    in February 1950 for renegotiation under the <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> of Cuban concessions on certain items negotiated originally in
                    1947; see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, January 9, 1950,
                    page 58. For information on the results of the renegotiations which concluded on
                    May 31, 1950, see <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, June 12, 1950, page 980.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
